===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# A family of [[language]]s spoken primarily in [[Iran]], [[Afghanistan]], [[Tajikistan]], and [[Uzbekistan]].

====Usage notes====
* Persian is the name applied to the official language of [[Iran]]. Varieties of this language are also spoken in [[Tajikistan]] and some parts of [[Afghanistan]] and [[Uzbekistan]]. The variety spoken in Afghanistan is called ''[[Dari]]'', and the variety spoken in Tajikistan is called ''[[Tajik]]'' or ''[[Tajiki]]''.
* The term ''[[Farsi]]'' (the local name for Persian) has recently developed currency in English to refer to the Persian language, especially the variety spoken in Iran.

